===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} ''polythéisme'' (ca. 1580), English from the early 17th century,
a learned formation from [[poly-]] ({{term|πολύς||many|tr=polús|lang=grc}}) and -[[theism]] ({{term|θεός||god|tr=theós|lang=grc}}) ({{prefix|poly|theism}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pɒliˈθiˈĭzˈəm/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The belief of the existence of many [[god]]s.

